      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلْمَرْأَةِ اَلَّتِي يُتَوَفَّى عَنْهَا زَوْجُهَا أَ تَحُجُّ فِي عِدَّتِهَا قَالَ «نَعَمْ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2914 - Ibn Bukayr narrated from Zurara, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a woman whose husband has passed away: \"Can she perform Hajj during her waiting period ('iddah)?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\""
        ]
      }
